\par Hallow
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Good]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 5, Drd 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M, DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  24 hours
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  40-ft. radius emanating from the touched point
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  See text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  See text
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Hallow }{\fs20\cf0 makes a particular site, building, or structure a holy site. This has four major effects.
\par First, the site or structure is guarded by a }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic circle against evil }{\fs20\cf0 effect.
\par Second, all Charisma checks made to turn undead gain a +4 sacred bonus, and Charisma checks to command undead take a \endash 4 penalty. Spell resistance does not apply to this effect. (This provision does not apply to the druid version of the spell.)

\par Third, any dead body interred in a }{\i\fs20\cf0 hallowed }{\fs20\cf0 site cannot be turned into an undead creature.
\par Finally, you may choose to fix a single spell effect to the }{\i\fs20\cf0 hallowed }{\fs20\cf0 site. The spell effect lasts for one year and functions throughout
 the entire site, regardless of the normal duration and area or effect. You may designate whether the effect applies to all creatures, creatures who share your faith or alignment, or creatures who adhere to another faith or alignment. At the end of the ye
ar, the chosen effect lapses, but it can be renewed or replaced simply by casting }{\i\fs20\cf0 hallow }{\fs20\cf0 again.
\par Spell effects that may be tied to a }{\i\fs20\cf0 hallowed }{\fs20\cf0 site include }{\i\fs20\cf0 aid, bane, bless, cause fear, darkness, daylight, death ward, deeper darkness, detect evil, detect magi
c, dimensional anchor, discern lies, dispel magic, endure elements, freedom of movement, invisibility purge, protection from energy, remove fear, resist energy, silence, tongues, }{\fs20\cf0 and }{\i\fs20\cf0 zone of truth}{\fs20\cf0 
. Saving throws and spell resistance might apply to these spells\rquote  effects. (See the individual spell descriptions for details.)
\par An area can receive only one }{\i\fs20\cf0 hallow }{\fs20\cf0 spell (and its associated spell effect) at a time. }{\i\fs20\cf0 Hallow }{\fs20\cf0 counters but does not dispel }{\i\fs20\cf0 unhallow}{\fs20\cf0 .
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 Herbs, oils, and incense worth at least 1,000 gp, plus 1,000 gp per level of the spell to be included in the }{\i\fs20\cf0 hallowed }{\fs20\cf0 area.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Hallucinatory Terrain
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Illusion (Glamer)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 4, Sor/Wiz 4
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  10 minutes
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Long (400 ft. + 40 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  One 30-ft. cube/level (S)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  2 hours/level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will disbelief (if interacted with)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par You make natural terrain look, sound, and smell like some other sort of natural terrain. Structures, equipment, and creatures within the area are not hidden or changed in appearance.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A stone, a twig, and a bit of green plant.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Halt Undead
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 3
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  Up to three undead creatures, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round/level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (see text)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This spell renders as many as three undead creatures immobile. A nonintelligent undead creature
 gets no saving throw; an intelligent undead creature does. If the spell is successful, it renders the undead creature immobile for the duration of the spell (similar to the effect of }{\i\fs20\cf0 hold person }{\fs20\cf0 
on a living creature). The effect is broken if the }{\i\fs20\cf0 halted }{\fs20\cf0 creatures are attacked or take damage.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A pinch of sulfur and powdered garlic.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Harm
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 6, Destruction 6
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will half; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Harm }{\fs20\cf0 charges a subject with negative energy that deals 10 points of damage per caster level (to a maximum of 150 points at 15th level). If the creature successfully saves, }{\i\fs20\cf0 harm }{\fs20\cf0 
deals half this amount, but it cannot reduce the target\rquote s hit points to less than 1.
\par If used on an undead creature, }{\i\fs20\cf0 harm }{\fs20\cf0 acts like }{\i\fs20\cf0 heal}{\fs20\cf0 .
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Haste
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 3, Sor/Wiz 3
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  One creature/level, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round/level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  Fortitude negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes (harmless)
\par The transmuted creatures move and act more quickly than normal. This extra speed has several effects.
\par When making a full attack action, a hasted creature may make one extra attack with any weapon he is holding. The attack is made using the creature\rquote s full base attack bonus, plus any modifiers appropriate to the situation. (This effect is not c
umulative with similar effects, such as that provided by a weapon of speed, nor does it actually grant an extra action, so you can\rquote t use it to cast a second spell or otherwise take an extra action in the round.)
\par A }{\i\fs20\cf0 hasted }{\fs20\cf0 creature gains a +1 bonus on attack rolls and a +1 dodge bonus to AC and Reflex saves. Any condition that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Armor Class (if any) also makes you lose dodge bonuses.
\par All of the }{\i\fs20\cf0 hasted }{\fs20\cf0 creature\rquote s modes of movement (including land movement, burrow, climb, fly, and swim) increase by 30 feet, to a maximum of twice the subject\rquote 
s normal speed using that form of movement. This increase counts as an enhancement bonus, and it affects the creature\rquote s jumping distance as normal for increased speed.
\par Multiple }{\i\fs20\cf0 haste }{\fs20\cf0 effects don\rquote t stack. }{\i\fs20\cf0 Haste }{\fs20\cf0 dispels and counters }{\i\fs20\cf0 slow.
\par Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A shaving of licorice root.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Heal
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Healing)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 6, Drd 7, Healing 6
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes (harmless)
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Heal }{\fs20\cf0 enables you to channel positive energy into a creature to wipe away injury and afflictions. It immediately ends any and all of the following adverse conditions affecting the Target: ability damage, blinded, }{\i\fs20\cf0 
confused, }{\fs20\cf0 dazed, dazzled, deafened, diseased, exhausted, fatigued, }{\i\fs20\cf0 feebleminded, }{\fs20\cf0 insanity, nauseated, sickened, stunned, and pois
oned. It also cures 10 hit points of damage per level of the caster, to a maximum of 150 points at 15th level.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Heal }{\fs20\cf0 does not remove negative levels, restore permanently drained levels, or restore permanently drained ability score points.
\par If used against an undead creature, }{\i\fs20\cf0 heal }{\fs20\cf0 instead acts like }{\i\fs20\cf0 harm}{\fs20\cf0 .
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Heal, Mass
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Healing)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 9, Healing 9
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  One or more creatures, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 heal, }{\fs20\cf0 except as noted above. The maximum number of hit points restored to each creature is 250.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Heal Mount
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Healing)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Pal 3
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Your mount touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes (harmless)
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 heal, }{\fs20\cf0 but it affects only the paladin\rquote s special mount (typically a warhorse).
